<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="judgement-n">judgement <strong><em>n</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /'dʒʌdʒmənt/    美 /'dʒʌdʒmənt/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>判断 (力)；辨别力</strong></h4>
<p>the ability to form opinions or to make sensible decisions：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He showed excellent judgement in choosing a friend. 
他在择友方面表现出了敏锐的判断力。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>意见；看法；评价</strong></h4>
<p>an opinion that you form after thinking carefully：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>make a judgement on / about</strong>
对…作出评价</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>In her judgment</strong>, it was a wrong thing to give children so much pocket money.
在她看来，给孩子们这么多零花钱是不对的。</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.<strong>审判</strong></h4></div>